INTERSHOP IOM 4.2.0-SNAPSHOT Database Model   (revision 0c3ab1b4a3dda5bf836ed9d229914e2fd345867c)

Table omt.CustomMenuItemDTO

Custom main menu items that should be displayed additionally.

Columns 

References[1] Column Type Constraints[2] Default Comment
id integer PK, UNIQUE, NOT_NULL nextval('"CustomMenuItemDTO_id_seq"')  
title varchar NOT_NULL The title of the item. Also a message key can be used. 
iconClass varchar The css-classes that should be used as icon. 
url varchar NOT_NULL The url the content of the item should be loaded from. 
rank integer The ascending order the items should be displayed in. 
active boolean NOT_NULL true Whether the item should be displayed. 
RightDefDO rightDefRef integer The permission that is required for this menu item. If not set, no permission is required. 
secure boolean NOT_NULL false Whether to enable requesting the url with security methods. 

[1] Not all references are enforced by a foreign key where they could.
Such "missing" foreign keys are denoted with [[ ]].

[2] Constraints:
PK : the column is part of the primary key
UNIQUE: does don't cover unique constraints and indexes defined on more than one column.

Constraints and Indexes 

Type Name Definition
PRIMARY KEY CustomMenuItemDTO_pk PRIMARY KEY (id) 
FOREIGN KEY CustomMenuItemDTO_fk_RightDefDO FOREIGN KEY ("rightDefRef") REFERENCES "RightDefDO"(id)
